Seems to have something to do with the depth of the stack - if that helps.
If I put a breakpoint in my main method, I will hit it no problem, and then I can step into other methods; but if I put a breakpoint in another method, I get the walkback.

import java.util.*;



public class MethodTest {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		Vector v= new Vector();

		v.addElement("v0");

		method1(v);

	}



	static void method1(Vector v) {

		v.addElement("v1");

		method2(v);

	}



	static void method2(Vector v) {

		v.addElement("v2");

	}

}
